Ahead  of the Ondo governorship election slated for October this year, the Action Democratic Party (ADP) and 14 other political parties have formed the third force to challenge the All Progressives Congress (APC) at the poll. The group at its maiden press briefing, said it is ready to wrestle power from the current APC-led government in the state. Addressing journalists in Akure on behalf of the political parties that formed “The Third Force”, Mr Biyi Poroye said the group parades arrays of experienced politicians.  Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Ahead of 2019, new parties yet to establish presence in states Suspense, last minute thrills as Ondo picks new governor ADP opts out of PDP-led coalition